comments.body:
@smartclayton @mrunalp Will port this to CRI-O once we have it working for podman.

General idea is to create the User Account on the fly for UIDs not in the container.  I could make this more simple by creating a new passwd file based off of the contents in the image and then add the line to it, and mount the new passwd file on /etc/passwd inside the container.  I think this would work well for OpenShift.

Problem on Podman would be that we would not be able to modify the /etc/passwd file and save it to an image, if the container is being run with a UID not in /etc/passwd in the container.
